## 🚀 STRATEGIC RECOVERY PLAN (Next Steps)

To reach the target of **150 GB+** free space, I recommend the following manual actions:

### Target A: Recover ~50-80 GB from WSL (Compaction)
Run these commands in a PowerShell (Admin) window when you don't need WSL:

```powershell
# 1. Shut down all WSL instances
wsl --shutdown

# 2. Compact the Ubuntu disk (Wait for it to finish)
# Note: Path may vary slightly, check its actual location in explorer first
diskpart
# In the diskpart prompt, type:
select vdisk file="C:\Users\gonya\AppData\Local\Packages\CanonicalGroupLimited.Ubuntu_79rhkp1fndgsc\LocalState\ext4.vhdx"
attach vdisk readonly
compact vdisk
detach vdisk
exit
```

### Target B: Recover ~100 GB from Steam (Migration)
Use the Steam Client to move games to another drive:
1. Open **Steam** → **Settings** → **Storage**.
2. Add a new drive (Select **G:\**).
3. Select large games on C:\ and click **Move**.

